title nasim — MCP-04 EXPOSE nasim Tools

' Participants with box colors per C4 layer

note over participants
  Scope:          Serving nasim tools via MCP server interface
  Preconditions:  MCPServerRuntime initialized, tools registered
  Excludes:       Tool discovery, adaptation (see MCP-02, MCP-03)
  Contexts:       External MCP client connection lifecycle
  Rollback:       Disconnect client on tool execution failure
  Design:         Request validation and rate limiting
end note

== MCP-04 EXPOSE nasim Tools ==

External MCP Client -> MCPServerRuntime: list_tools()
MCPServerRuntime -> ToolRegistry: get_all_tools()
ToolRegistry --> MCPServerRuntime: tool_list
MCPServerRuntime --> External MCP Client: tool_definitions
External MCP Client -> MCPServerRuntime: call_tool(name, args)
MCPServerRuntime -> ToolRegistry: execute(name, args)
ToolRegistry --> MCPServerRuntime: result
MCPServerRuntime --> External MCP Client: tool_result

note over participants
  Flow:    Client lists tools -> calls tool -> server executes -> returns result
  State:   idle -> processing -> complete
  Failure: Tool not found -> error response; execution failure -> error response
  Success: Client receives tool execution result
end note

@enduml